CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 6, 1957, pg. A8, reads: "Tots Model Fashions - These little tots, well known in the 3300 block of Webster Ave., modeled fashions for the younger set at the lawn party sponsored by the 3300 Club. The tots were just a small part of the gala program at which Mrs. Toki Schalk Johnson of The Courier was the commentator. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six boys, including one in center wearing Boy Scouts uniform, and nine girls, fashion models for lawn party fashion show sponsored by 3300 Club, 3300 block of Webster Avenue, Hill District
